exercises.name: Push-up
exercises.description: A bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

exercises.name: Bench Press
exercises.description: A compound exercise that involves pressing a weight upwards from a supine position, targeting the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

exercises.name: Chest Fly
exercises.description: An isolation exercise that targets the chest muscles by bringing the arms together in front of the body.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl
exercises.description: An isolation exercise targeting the biceps, performed by curling the weight up towards the shoulder.

exercises.name: Tricep Dip
exercises.description: A compound exercise that targets the triceps, performed by dipping the body down and pushing it back up using the arms.

exercises.name: Squat
exercises.description: A compound exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes by lowering the body into a seated position and standing back up.

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.description: A compound exercise that targets the lower back, hamstrings, and glutes by lifting a weighted barbell or dumbbells from the ground to a standing position.

exercises.name: Pull-up
exercises.description: An upper body exercise targeting the back muscles, performed by pulling oneself up to a bar.

exercises.name: Shoulder Press
exercises.description: An exercise targeting the deltoid muscles, performed by pressing a weight overhead from shoulder height to full extension.

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.description: A resistance machine exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes.

exercises.name: Barbell Row
exercises.description: An exercise targeting the upper back and lats, performed by pulling a weighted barbell towards the torso.

exercises.name: Lateral Raise
exercises.description: An isolation exercise targeting the deltoid muscles, performed by raising the arms laterally to shoulder height.
